        "body": "Yes we had the same idea, see https://github.com/gjoseph92/dask/commit/b9a0d927541de969ebf6053fbbbcca65afe9cf28 :)\r\n\r\nIt does work when the DataFrame has 1 partition. However see the note on that commit: because array <--> dataframe operations require both inputs to have the same chunk pattern, we'd need to know the number of (aligned) partitions of the other input DataFrames first, so we could pass that into `from_array`.",
